1
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:36,911
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

2
00:00:37,411 --> 00:00:38,579
About yesterday.

3
00:00:39,413 --> 00:00:40,790
Yesterday?

4
00:00:41,040 --> 00:00:43,209
- Yeah, when we kissed.
- What?

5
00:00:43,459 --> 00:00:46,420
I was so excited to see you again
that I couldn't even sleep at night.

6
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:47,547
Did you sleep well?

7
00:00:51,884 --> 00:00:53,010
Is he serious?

8
00:00:53,678 --> 00:00:54,679
Did you kiss him?

9
00:00:56,597 --> 00:00:57,640
Yeah, I did.

10
00:00:57,723 --> 00:01:01,852
But why should I have to admit it
in public like this?

11
00:01:02,144 --> 00:01:03,563
Are you going to stand there?

12
00:01:03,771 --> 00:01:05,690
We'd like to have a private conversation.

13
00:01:17,785 --> 00:01:22,164
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE
EPISODE 5

14
00:01:22,915 --> 00:01:26,210
What's the important thing
he wants to say? Is it...

15
00:01:28,337 --> 00:01:31,507
I know we took a while,
but we found each other again.

16
00:01:32,383 --> 00:01:34,427
- And we even kissed.
- I'm not the type

17
00:01:34,510 --> 00:01:36,178
- to change my mind
- He sounds

18
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:38,139
- like he's about to ask me out.
- but will you work with me?

19
00:01:38,222 --> 00:01:39,265
What should I say?

20
00:01:39,473 --> 00:01:42,184
Should we start dating first,
then get to know each other?

21
00:01:43,394 --> 00:01:44,395
Ui-yeong?

22
00:01:45,438 --> 00:01:47,064
So, do you want to work with me?

23
00:01:48,899 --> 00:01:51,110
Oh, do what together?

24
00:01:53,070 --> 00:01:56,490
Eun-ho brought me this
along with my stuff yesterday.

25
00:01:56,574 --> 00:01:57,950
DAD AND UNCLE

26
00:01:58,034 --> 00:02:02,079
Oh, yeah, Sua is great at sketching.

27
00:02:02,747 --> 00:02:04,040
What about it, though?

28
00:02:04,123 --> 00:02:07,293
Well, she doodled
where she shouldn't have.

29
00:02:07,376 --> 00:02:09,045
WOOD AND SPIRITS NIGHT
WHISKEY BRAND POP-UP PROPOSAL

30
00:02:15,676 --> 00:02:17,803
The hotel's losing out on a lot
from this deal.

31
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:20,139
You guys offered whatever budget we needed

32
00:02:20,222 --> 00:02:22,058
to follow the proposal.

33
00:02:22,308 --> 00:02:24,560
And we loved the new idea
about making special suites

34
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:26,479
using our furniture from the pop-up.

35
00:02:26,562 --> 00:02:29,023
This would smoothly introduce
our furniture to the guests.

36
00:02:29,106 --> 00:02:32,485
Furniture makers are always thirsty
for a chance to prove

37
00:02:32,568 --> 00:02:35,613
how sturdy their products are,
instead of just how pretty they are.

38
00:02:38,783 --> 00:02:39,950
I'm sorry

39
00:02:40,368 --> 00:02:43,746
for getting angry at you
instead of giving you a chance to explain.

40
00:02:44,747 --> 00:02:47,958
Don't feel bad.
I'm so glad you've changed your mind.

41
00:02:49,377 --> 00:02:51,629
I look forward to working with you.

42
00:02:52,505 --> 00:02:54,340
- Me too.
- I'll contact the brand

43
00:02:54,423 --> 00:02:57,093
to confirm the design
and schedule a kick-off meeting.

44
00:02:57,218 --> 00:02:59,887
How's your schedule?
We'd like a meeting as soon as possible.

45
00:03:00,763 --> 00:03:02,306
Let me check my schedule.

46
00:03:02,431 --> 00:03:04,850
Sounds good. Let's see...

47
00:03:07,019 --> 00:03:10,147
We're free on Monday at the earliest.

48
00:03:13,109 --> 00:03:14,568
See you.

49
00:03:14,694 --> 00:03:16,529
By the way

50
00:03:18,489 --> 00:03:19,532
the ki...

51
00:03:21,033 --> 00:03:22,368
The ki...

52
00:03:22,493 --> 00:03:23,536
"Ki"?

53
00:03:24,078 --> 00:03:27,540
Key ring! No, cream!
You have cream on your face.

54
00:03:27,623 --> 00:03:28,708
Oh, here?

55
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:31,085
It must be the latte.

56
00:03:32,044 --> 00:03:33,295
What I mean is...

57
00:03:34,380 --> 00:03:35,423
You know...

58
00:03:36,215 --> 00:03:38,092
The ki...

59
00:03:38,884 --> 00:03:39,885
Oh, there's my key.

60
00:03:40,803 --> 00:03:41,804
Ta-da!

61
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:43,556
Oh, sure.

62
00:03:46,684 --> 00:03:48,185
See you around, then.

63
00:03:48,310 --> 00:03:49,353
Bye.

64
00:03:55,568 --> 00:03:57,778
Why do I have cream on my face
when I had a latte?

65
00:04:00,072 --> 00:04:01,240
So

66
00:04:02,241 --> 00:04:04,910
that's all he has to say about our kiss?

67
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:19,341
What was I even saying?

68
00:04:22,303 --> 00:04:23,596
They kissed?

69
00:04:28,601 --> 00:04:31,562
Wood is finicky.

70
00:04:32,104 --> 00:04:36,275
It contracts or expands,
depending on temperature and humidity.

71
00:04:36,484 --> 00:04:39,653
Sometimes, that causes faults
in furniture.

72
00:04:42,823 --> 00:04:44,241
- What?
- Sorry?

73
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:45,409
- What?
- What?

74
00:04:45,493 --> 00:04:46,535
What was that?

75
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:47,995
Oh, my point is

76
00:04:48,078 --> 00:04:51,749
we offer free repairs for a year.

77
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:54,168
Yes.

78
00:04:55,586 --> 00:04:58,839
I WANT TO GO TO YOUR HOUSE AFTER WORK

79
00:05:00,758 --> 00:05:03,427
You have nothing to worry about.

80
00:05:03,677 --> 00:05:05,763
Take your time
and look through the catalog.

81
00:05:13,437 --> 00:05:15,815
I didn't know you were such a brave guy.

82
00:05:15,898 --> 00:05:17,650
Everyone in heaven must be talking!

83
00:05:17,733 --> 00:05:19,860
How could you kiss her inside a church?

84
00:05:19,944 --> 00:05:21,862
I didn't think it through.

85
00:05:21,946 --> 00:05:24,573
With the kiss and when I brought it up.

86
00:05:25,991 --> 00:05:28,244
I did both because I wasn't thinking!

87
00:05:28,661 --> 00:05:29,954
Good job.

88
00:05:30,037 --> 00:05:33,624
Nothing seals the deal better than a kiss.

89
00:05:33,874 --> 00:05:35,376
Now that you've sealed the deal

90
00:05:35,459 --> 00:05:37,044
don't even think about running away.

91
00:05:37,127 --> 00:05:39,380
- Be responsible...
- Uncle! Dad!

92
00:05:39,547 --> 00:05:41,173
What? Were you listening?

93
00:05:41,757 --> 00:05:44,510
My headphones don't have noise-canceling.

94
00:05:46,011 --> 00:05:47,012
Sua

95
00:05:47,388 --> 00:05:48,806
you know

96
00:05:48,889 --> 00:05:51,767
Uncle kissed someone.

97
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:54,645
You know, like how we kiss.

98
00:05:54,854 --> 00:05:57,940
You kissed her? So, you're dating now?

99
00:05:58,482 --> 00:06:00,317
- Basically.
- That was a trick question.

100
00:06:00,401 --> 00:06:03,112
You realize things are different now,
right?

101
00:06:03,279 --> 00:06:05,281
A kiss doesn't mean you're committed.

102
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:07,533
Did you hurt her? Or break anything?

103
00:06:07,700 --> 00:06:11,203
I think I'm broken.

104
00:06:11,287 --> 00:06:14,164
No, you're not. You're just soft now.

105
00:06:14,248 --> 00:06:16,500
That's what happens when you like someone.

106
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:19,461
Oh, good point.

107
00:06:19,545 --> 00:06:20,880
I'd forgotten how it felt.

108
00:06:20,963 --> 00:06:24,550
Congrats, Uncle. Falling for someone is
something to celebrate.

109
00:06:25,801 --> 00:06:27,469
So, what's your plan now?

110
00:06:29,555 --> 00:06:30,806
I'll work hard

111
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:33,392
and ask her out on a proper date.

112
00:06:33,475 --> 00:06:34,518
Good luck!

113
00:06:34,602 --> 00:06:36,478
Tell me if things go well.

114
00:06:36,562 --> 00:06:38,355
And tell me if things don't go well.

115
00:06:38,439 --> 00:06:40,983
You know we're always on your side, right?

116
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:44,778
You got it!

117
00:06:51,702 --> 00:06:55,664
Sua, how do you know this so well?

118
00:06:55,873 --> 00:06:57,333
Have you had a boyfriend?

119
00:06:59,376 --> 00:07:00,711
I know you can hear me.

120
00:07:01,420 --> 00:07:05,549
Promise me you'll ask me for permission
before dating anyone, okay?

121
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:07,468
Not that I'll ever let you date!

122
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:10,429
You don't have a boyfriend, right?

123
00:07:37,331 --> 00:07:38,958
He's our Executive Director.

124
00:07:39,208 --> 00:07:40,834
And they're HOME representatives.

125
00:07:41,001 --> 00:07:42,336
I'm Song Tae-seop.

126
00:07:43,420 --> 00:07:44,880
I'm Lee Eun-ho.

127
00:07:51,595 --> 00:07:52,680
Everything's ready.

128
00:07:53,138 --> 00:07:54,181
Here.

129
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:55,891
- Hello.
- Nice to meet you.

130
00:07:56,308 --> 00:07:57,851
I look forward to working with you.

131
00:08:04,149 --> 00:08:06,151
It's been a minute, Mr. Kang.

132
00:08:06,235 --> 00:08:07,444
- Hello.
- Hi.

133
00:08:08,153 --> 00:08:11,615
I heard there was an incident
in the bidding process.

134
00:08:11,824 --> 00:08:14,159
Thank you for giving us a second chance.

135
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:15,911
We understand.

136
00:08:15,995 --> 00:08:18,956
I hope the two companies can now focus
on the project.

137
00:08:19,039 --> 00:08:20,499
We don't hold grudges.

138
00:08:24,294 --> 00:08:25,963
This is the theme for the pop-up.

139
00:08:26,213 --> 00:08:29,133
Our motif is a local bar
showcasing Deerfiddich's heritage

140
00:08:29,216 --> 00:08:31,010
and its perfect first sip

141
00:08:31,093 --> 00:08:32,594
that hasn't changed in 100 years.

142
00:08:32,678 --> 00:08:36,181
But we'll put a clean, modern twist
in the photo zone and the mini bar

143
00:08:36,265 --> 00:08:38,517
which will lead to an exhibition
of the brand history.

144
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:42,021
Our goal is to provide an experience
to enjoy the whiskey with all senses.

145
00:08:48,318 --> 00:08:50,070
In the second exhibition

146
00:08:50,154 --> 00:08:53,115
we'll display whiskey
at different aging levels

147
00:08:53,198 --> 00:08:56,410
and explain the charm at each level.

148
00:08:57,661 --> 00:08:59,329
We look forward to working with you.

149
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:02,124
Try to support HOME
with everything they need.

150
00:09:02,207 --> 00:09:04,334
- Yes, sir.
- Pleased to be working with you.

151
00:09:11,592 --> 00:09:12,676
I asked my team

152
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:15,929
to make sure the food was extra good.
How is it?

153
00:09:16,013 --> 00:09:17,139
It's delicious.

154
00:09:17,222 --> 00:09:19,266
I'm so glad. Please enjoy it.

155
00:09:19,475 --> 00:09:23,729
Mr. Song, why did you change your mind?
You didn't want to work with us.

156
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:27,691
It's all thanks to Ms. Lee.

157
00:09:32,154 --> 00:09:36,033
Mr. Song always leaves out key details
and gives the wrong message.

158
00:09:36,116 --> 00:09:40,204
He means that Ms. Lee's passion
changed our minds.

159
00:09:42,331 --> 00:09:45,667
I've never seen anyone make towel animals
as well as she does!

160
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:49,379
Ms. Lee has a humorous way of working,
doesn't she?

161
00:09:49,463 --> 00:09:50,464
For sure.

162
00:09:50,547 --> 00:09:54,760
So, we'd like to keep her
as our main point of contact.

163
00:09:54,843 --> 00:09:57,429
- Oh, well...
- Sure, if that's what you want.

164
00:09:57,513 --> 00:09:59,515
I'll be in touch with Deerfiddich.

165
00:09:59,598 --> 00:10:02,351
That'll be fine, as long as she keeps me
in the loop.

166
00:10:02,434 --> 00:10:03,477
Okay.

167
00:10:03,685 --> 00:10:07,231
Please let me know anytime
if you need anything.

168
00:10:07,564 --> 00:10:08,565
Okay.

169
00:10:09,525 --> 00:10:11,151
- Eat up.
- Yes, sir.

170
00:10:15,114 --> 00:10:18,325
You'll need to set up the pop-up booth
and the guest suites simultaneously.

171
00:10:18,742 --> 00:10:21,161
I'm worried about the tight schedule.

172
00:10:21,537 --> 00:10:22,621
I know.

173
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:25,332
Since we're going to be too busy for now

174
00:10:25,415 --> 00:10:27,709
do you want to go on a date
once the project's over?

175
00:10:28,001 --> 00:10:29,002
A date?

176
00:10:31,755 --> 00:10:33,340
Sorry, it's just that we're at work.

177
00:10:33,423 --> 00:10:34,550
Right.

178
00:10:36,051 --> 00:10:38,679
I don't think anyone heard me, thankfully.

179
00:10:40,013 --> 00:10:41,014
So, is that a yes?

180
00:10:43,475 --> 00:10:44,476
Yes.

181
00:10:51,775 --> 00:10:54,111
"Cherry up!" "Get a grape on yourself."

182
00:10:55,112 --> 00:10:57,990
"What are you even celery-brating?"
"Don't get so melon-cholic."

183
00:10:58,782 --> 00:10:59,825
Sorry?

184
00:11:00,284 --> 00:11:02,703
Look at the signs. They're so funny.

185
00:11:02,786 --> 00:11:04,288
WHAT ARE YOU EVEN CELERY-BRATING?

186
00:11:05,372 --> 00:11:06,623
GET A GRAPE ON YOURSELF

187
00:11:06,707 --> 00:11:07,875
GOING BANANAS FOR ME YET?

188
00:11:08,542 --> 00:11:11,044
Why don't we grab some coffee
before heading back?

189
00:11:11,211 --> 00:11:12,421
Sounds good.

190
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:19,011
You know the chicken feet we had?
I keep thinking about them.

191
00:11:19,469 --> 00:11:20,804
At first

192
00:11:21,346 --> 00:11:23,807
I didn't even understand
how I was supposed to eat them.

193
00:11:24,391 --> 00:11:26,268
People don't eat them outside Korea,
do they?

194
00:11:26,435 --> 00:11:29,813
But there's no way out
once you get addicted to the spice.

195
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:32,107
Please invite me
to the Eat Eat Club again.

196
00:11:32,191 --> 00:11:33,442
Will do.

197
00:11:34,568 --> 00:11:35,736
We'd better head back.

198
00:11:35,819 --> 00:11:38,947
I need to get some coffee for my team.
You can go first.

199
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:40,574
- Thanks for today.
- It's nothing.

200
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:52,544
- Hey, Ui-yeong.
- Hey, Hyun-min, I'm getting coffee

201
00:11:52,628 --> 00:11:54,504
for you and Sae-byeok. What do you want?

202
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:57,049
Two iced Americanos, please.

203
00:11:57,132 --> 00:11:59,009
Oh, and a sandwich, too.

204
00:11:59,259 --> 00:12:01,386
Huh? Have you not had lunch yet?

205
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:03,138
I have, but not Sae-byeok.

206
00:12:03,222 --> 00:12:05,933
She feels too guilty to have lunch.

207
00:12:06,266 --> 00:12:09,353
Oh, really? Okay, I got it.

208
00:12:26,662 --> 00:12:28,580
Did you just come to work?

209
00:12:28,664 --> 00:12:31,333
Yeah, I work from 6 p.m. until closing
from Monday to Wednesday

210
00:12:31,792 --> 00:12:34,044
and from 1 p.m. to 6 p.m.
on Thursdays and Fridays.

211
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:35,712
So

212
00:12:36,046 --> 00:12:37,965
you're working
with the blind date guy now?

213
00:12:38,048 --> 00:12:41,802
I didn't know it,
but his company participated in our bid.

214
00:12:41,885 --> 00:12:43,262
What a coincidence, right?

215
00:12:46,348 --> 00:12:47,557
Yeah, that's cool.

216
00:12:48,016 --> 00:12:49,643
So, are you two dating now?

217
00:12:52,354 --> 00:12:54,481
No, we're not there yet.

218
00:12:56,358 --> 00:12:57,401
That's the spirit!

219
00:12:57,567 --> 00:12:59,945
What are you, 20?
One kiss, and you're all his? No way.

220
00:13:01,071 --> 00:13:03,198
I've had my fair share of kisses

221
00:13:03,282 --> 00:13:06,201
maybe even 500 of them,
including those in plays.

222
00:13:06,535 --> 00:13:09,871
Once you start overthinking it,
it leads to unnecessary feelings.

223
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:13,166
I could even kiss you right now.

224
00:13:15,460 --> 00:13:16,712
What the hell are you doing?

225
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,592
And I know a kiss isn't everything

226
00:13:22,676 --> 00:13:25,387
but it doesn't mean it's nothing.

227
00:13:26,054 --> 00:13:28,140
What kind of a life have you lived
to think that?

228
00:13:28,223 --> 00:13:29,891
I lived a pretty normal life.

229
00:13:35,314 --> 00:13:38,775
How does it feel to ride a motorcycle?

230
00:13:39,901 --> 00:13:42,321
It feels like you're cutting the world
with scissors.

231
00:13:43,822 --> 00:13:44,823
"Cutting the world"?

232
00:13:44,906 --> 00:13:46,658
You want a ride to see it for yourself?

233
00:13:46,825 --> 00:13:49,036
Yeah, I'd love that! Next time.

234
00:13:51,371 --> 00:13:58,879
BREAK ROOM

235
00:14:08,263 --> 00:14:11,058
Your internship's over soon, right?

236
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:13,060
I just happened to see your contract.

237
00:14:13,143 --> 00:14:15,270
Yeah, it's over in a month.

238
00:14:15,729 --> 00:14:17,939
Let's be honest.

239
00:14:18,398 --> 00:14:21,818
Working at a hotel feels fancy,
but the pay is so low.

240
00:14:22,194 --> 00:14:24,404
Your starting salary is everything.

241
00:14:24,488 --> 00:14:26,865
I have a close friend who's a banker.

242
00:14:26,948 --> 00:14:29,117
He could give you some advice.

243
00:14:29,534 --> 00:14:31,578
Why don't I introduce you to him?

244
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:33,914
I'll take care of it myself.

245
00:14:35,457 --> 00:14:36,458
Okay.

246
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:40,045
Where are you, my lazy intern?
Come to the Conference Room.

247
00:14:40,128 --> 00:14:42,381
I have to go. Ui-yeong is looking for me.

248
00:14:42,798 --> 00:14:44,716
- Please excuse me.
- Okay.

249
00:14:53,725 --> 00:14:55,685
You've been on a diet lately, haven't you?

250
00:14:56,269 --> 00:14:58,730
What? No, I'm not.

251
00:14:58,814 --> 00:15:01,400
Or is working here so hard
that you've lost your appetite?

252
00:15:01,483 --> 00:15:04,277
It's okay. Work gets hard sometimes.

253
00:15:04,361 --> 00:15:06,321
You learned a big lesson this time.

254
00:15:06,405 --> 00:15:09,199
You must be so disappointed in me.

255
00:15:09,366 --> 00:15:11,326
I can't be disappointed
from just one mistake.

256
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:12,536
It's time for you

257
00:15:12,619 --> 00:15:15,664
to learn how much energy food gives you

258
00:15:15,747 --> 00:15:16,998
even when you force it down.

259
00:15:17,999 --> 00:15:19,543
Thank you.

260
00:15:19,626 --> 00:15:21,670
Eat this, cheer up, and help me.

261
00:15:22,003 --> 00:15:23,672
- Sorry?
- I want you

262
00:15:23,755 --> 00:15:26,049
to back me up
on all tasks related to the pop-up.

263
00:15:26,133 --> 00:15:27,175
Me?

264
00:15:28,468 --> 00:15:32,264
But HOME wouldn't want to work with me.

265
00:15:32,347 --> 00:15:35,517
If I were them, I would've liked you less
if you ran away after one mistake.

266
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:38,645
And I'd give another chance to someone
who tries to make up for it.

267
00:15:39,813 --> 00:15:41,273
Ui-yeong!

268
00:15:41,356 --> 00:15:42,816
You'll stay strong, right?

269
00:15:43,108 --> 00:15:45,152
Yeah, I can do it!

270
00:15:46,736 --> 00:15:48,447
Alright, who wants to go first?

271
00:16:02,669 --> 00:16:03,795
Let me keep it short.

272
00:16:03,879 --> 00:16:07,048
How many people do you think use cabinets
for their stuff at a hotel?

273
00:16:07,132 --> 00:16:09,593
- Think of something more practical.
- Okay.

274
00:16:09,676 --> 00:16:11,761
And you two need to check
the layout again first.

275
00:16:11,970 --> 00:16:13,346
There's no space for big pieces.

276
00:16:13,430 --> 00:16:15,682
I stayed up for multiple nights,
looking at the layout

277
00:16:15,765 --> 00:16:18,101
and the suite is too small
with so many items already.

278
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:22,647
Mr. Song, this layout is like a canvas
that's already full.

279
00:16:25,942 --> 00:16:27,569
I know it's not easy.

280
00:16:28,028 --> 00:16:29,237
Let's wrap it up for today.

281
00:16:29,654 --> 00:16:31,114
You can go home early and rest.

282
00:16:31,448 --> 00:16:32,741
- Okay.
- Okay.

283
00:17:01,561 --> 00:17:04,064
Man this is so heavy!

284
00:17:04,147 --> 00:17:06,900
You can get the best prices
on the Internet!

285
00:17:07,859 --> 00:17:10,403
Look up what you need,
list the items by price, order

286
00:17:10,487 --> 00:17:12,030
and they'll arrive the next morning.

287
00:17:12,113 --> 00:17:14,533
But I feel better
when I check the products myself.

288
00:17:14,616 --> 00:17:16,535
I can check the expiration dates

289
00:17:16,743 --> 00:17:19,079
and check on my good old friend
while I'm at it.

290
00:17:19,704 --> 00:17:21,289
And make your friend a pack mule?

291
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:23,583
Thank you, friend.

292
00:17:25,043 --> 00:17:28,129
So, how's working with your date?

293
00:17:28,213 --> 00:17:29,798
Huh? Oh, the project?

294
00:17:29,923 --> 00:17:32,133
All we do is work.

295
00:17:32,342 --> 00:17:34,427
I want to message him first and all

296
00:17:34,511 --> 00:17:36,555
but I know he's super busy, so I can't.

297
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:39,766
How nice would it be
for him to message me first?

298
00:17:39,849 --> 00:17:41,643
- We even kissed...
- What did you say?

299
00:17:43,103 --> 00:17:45,689
You kissed him? When?

300
00:17:47,857 --> 00:17:49,818
Huh? Well...

301
00:17:49,901 --> 00:17:52,612
It was just in the heat of the moment.

302
00:17:52,696 --> 00:17:54,322
One thing led to another.

303
00:17:54,948 --> 00:17:56,324
Are you going to lecture me?

304
00:17:58,785 --> 00:18:00,495
No, who am I to do that?

305
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:03,832
You know the girl I sold my comics to?

306
00:18:03,915 --> 00:18:04,958
What?

307
00:18:05,959 --> 00:18:07,669
Never mind. It's nothing.

308
00:18:08,253 --> 00:18:09,421
You want to work out?

309
00:18:09,504 --> 00:18:12,048
I just worked out! And I'm exhausted.

310
00:18:13,008 --> 00:18:14,509
This is my pay for the day.

311
00:18:14,718 --> 00:18:17,053
- Bye.
- Get home safely. Thank you!

312
00:18:17,137 --> 00:18:18,221
Bye.

313
00:18:23,727 --> 00:18:25,061
- Huh?
- Ui-yeong

314
00:18:25,145 --> 00:18:26,855
can we meet tomorrow?

315
00:18:26,938 --> 00:18:29,232
What? He really messaged me.

316
00:18:39,159 --> 00:18:40,910
Yeah, little pecks are great.

317
00:18:42,245 --> 00:18:44,789
Pecks lead to kisses

318
00:18:45,915 --> 00:18:47,000
and kisses...

319
00:18:49,002 --> 00:18:52,672
It's rare to hit it off so well
on the first try.

320
00:18:57,469 --> 00:18:58,511
Hmm?

321
00:19:06,519 --> 00:19:08,438
I had to leave first because of work.

322
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:22,661
I've never had a man tidy my home
after a night together like that.

323
00:19:24,496 --> 00:19:25,914
What did she just say?

324
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:27,874
I don't know.

325
00:19:36,091 --> 00:19:37,425
- Hello.
- Yeah?

326
00:19:37,509 --> 00:19:39,010
Do you have a minute?

327
00:19:39,094 --> 00:19:41,471
Seven, eight, nine, ten.

328
00:19:44,265 --> 00:19:46,851
It's your last personal training session.

329
00:19:47,227 --> 00:19:49,521
Did you feel yourself get stronger
after the sessions?

330
00:19:49,604 --> 00:19:51,690
I lost a pound or two.

331
00:19:51,773 --> 00:19:54,192
But I can lose that much
just by going to the bathroom.

332
00:19:55,235 --> 00:19:57,028
Losing a pound or two

333
00:19:57,112 --> 00:19:59,739
with more muscle mass and less fat is

334
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:01,991
a huge achievement.

335
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:04,119
Now that you've built a good habit...

336
00:20:04,202 --> 00:20:06,913
But I could really notice
the money leaving my account.

337
00:20:06,996 --> 00:20:10,291
Gosh, my husband nags me about it
all the time!

338
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:12,794
Bring your husband next time, then.

339
00:20:12,877 --> 00:20:14,337
I'll make sure he doesn't nag...

340
00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:16,381
No, don't cause trouble in my family.

341
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:19,467
- You're getting a lot of messages.
- Sorry.

342
00:20:20,969 --> 00:20:22,345
Goodbye!

343
00:20:22,429 --> 00:20:23,680
Wait!

344
00:20:24,681 --> 00:20:26,099
Hey...

345
00:20:32,939 --> 00:20:34,023
What are you doing?

346
00:20:34,107 --> 00:20:35,942
I'm sure you thought of me at least once.

347
00:20:36,025 --> 00:20:37,277
You want to meet tonight?

348
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:38,695
No way.

349
00:20:39,612 --> 00:20:40,739
Did she notice it?

350
00:21:04,929 --> 00:21:08,057
I should've told her honestly!
That would've been less embarrassing.

351
00:21:08,391 --> 00:21:10,059
BIG DISCOUNTS

352
00:21:10,143 --> 00:21:11,853
I'm busy tonight.

353
00:21:11,936 --> 00:21:13,605
What happened that night was a mistake.

354
00:21:14,063 --> 00:21:15,857
Please don't get mad.

355
00:21:15,940 --> 00:21:17,275
SOONMU PAY

356
00:21:17,358 --> 00:21:18,526
SEND MONEY

357
00:21:20,111 --> 00:21:21,279
SEND MONEY TO BIG DISCOUNTS

358
00:21:21,821 --> 00:21:22,947
15,000 won.

359
00:21:23,031 --> 00:21:25,784
SEND 15,000 WON TO BIG DISCOUNTS

360
00:21:25,867 --> 00:21:26,910
Is that too much?

361
00:21:28,953 --> 00:21:31,456
How about 10,000 won?

362
00:21:31,706 --> 00:21:32,999
PLEASE ENTER YOUR PASSWORD

363
00:21:33,541 --> 00:21:35,502
Could you check this equipment?

364
00:21:35,752 --> 00:21:36,795
Coming!

365
00:21:38,922 --> 00:21:40,465
YOU RECEIVED 10,000 WON

366
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:45,345
Did he just send me money? Is he crazy?

367
00:21:45,762 --> 00:21:46,930
This son of a...

368
00:21:48,473 --> 00:21:51,643
Is his brain made of mush or what?
This moron!

369
00:21:52,685 --> 00:21:53,895
You're dead!

370
00:22:21,965 --> 00:22:23,508
Hello, Deukgeun Deukgeun Gym.

371
00:22:23,758 --> 00:22:26,678
Sorry?
Isn't this Mr. Lim Seung-jun's number?

372
00:22:29,222 --> 00:22:31,599
Yeah, that's me. Who is this?

373
00:22:31,766 --> 00:22:33,601
We're calling from Soonmu Market.

374
00:22:33,685 --> 00:22:35,353
Did you recently sell comic books?

375
00:22:35,436 --> 00:22:37,814
The buyer just filed a report against you.

376
00:22:37,981 --> 00:22:41,025
Did you make inappropriate comments
and scam the buyer?

377
00:22:41,359 --> 00:22:42,402
Sorry?

378
00:22:42,485 --> 00:22:43,820
WHY THE HELL DID YOU SEND ME MONEY?

379
00:22:43,903 --> 00:22:45,405
ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND?

380
00:22:45,488 --> 00:22:46,781
AM I A JOKE TO YOU?
JUST BECAUSE I SLEPT WITH YOU?

381
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:47,949
ANSWER ME, YOU JERK! WHAT ARE YOU, SCARED?

382
00:22:48,575 --> 00:22:49,617
Oh, gosh.

383
00:22:50,535 --> 00:22:51,953
YOU WANT ME TO BREAK YOUR NECK?

384
00:22:52,036 --> 00:22:53,162
What's all this?

385
00:22:56,457 --> 00:22:57,667
- Ui-yeong!
- Yeah?

386
00:22:59,586 --> 00:23:02,839
This is the list of sample whiskies
and recipes for the pop-up.

387
00:23:02,922 --> 00:23:04,048
Okay.

388
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:06,509
Sae-byeok, have you found a bartender?

389
00:23:06,593 --> 00:23:07,969
Yes, I have.

390
00:23:08,052 --> 00:23:09,971
I'll e-mail his profile to you.

391
00:23:10,054 --> 00:23:11,389
- Alright.
- Perfect.

392
00:23:14,309 --> 00:23:18,354
Ms. Big Discounts,
I didn't mean to offend you.

393
00:23:18,438 --> 00:23:20,982
I'd like to apologize to you.
Do you have time today?

394
00:23:21,065 --> 00:23:24,193
So, he wants to fight in person?

395
00:23:24,485 --> 00:23:26,362
- The comic book seller?
- Yeah.

396
00:23:26,738 --> 00:23:29,616
Turns out, he's the biggest scumbag!
Absolute garbage.

397
00:23:30,575 --> 00:23:32,535
- The comic books?
- No, the seller.

398
00:23:32,619 --> 00:23:34,454
It's like he slept
through sex ed, literature

399
00:23:34,537 --> 00:23:36,331
and when his mom taught him manners.

400
00:23:36,414 --> 00:23:38,666
I'll teach you a lesson today.

401
00:23:40,501 --> 00:23:41,878
SONG TAE-SEOP

402
00:23:46,507 --> 00:23:47,717
Hi, Mr. Song.

403
00:23:49,344 --> 00:23:50,428
Right now?

404
00:23:51,596 --> 00:23:53,598
Oh, you'll come to the office?

405
00:24:03,441 --> 00:24:05,360
Is this the only cafe around here?

406
00:24:08,112 --> 00:24:09,322
Here are your drinks.

407
00:24:09,530 --> 00:24:10,782
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

408
00:24:10,865 --> 00:24:12,367
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

409
00:24:13,868 --> 00:24:15,620
Do you have a girlfriend?

410
00:24:15,703 --> 00:24:16,704
It's a secret.

411
00:24:16,788 --> 00:24:18,206
- Tell us!
- Come on.

412
00:24:18,289 --> 00:24:20,375
She brought us both here today.

413
00:24:20,458 --> 00:24:22,001
Come three more times. I'll do that.

414
00:24:22,085 --> 00:24:23,670
- Man!
- That's so mean.

415
00:24:23,753 --> 00:24:25,338
- Three more times?
- Hello...

416
00:24:27,590 --> 00:24:29,217
You're here. Again.

417
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:30,301
Yeah.

418
00:24:30,677 --> 00:24:33,388
I didn't know the barista had favorites
among customers here.

419
00:24:33,638 --> 00:24:36,015
What do you know? I'm only human.

420
00:24:36,265 --> 00:24:37,976
I'm less glad to see some than others.

421
00:24:38,059 --> 00:24:39,435
- Right?
- Yeah.

422
00:24:40,019 --> 00:24:43,106
Four iced Americanos to go, please.

423
00:24:46,484 --> 00:24:48,611
Sorry about my white lie last time.

424
00:24:49,112 --> 00:24:50,780
You know I'm not her cousin, right?

425
00:24:52,490 --> 00:24:53,992
Yeah, but I don't care.

426
00:24:57,829 --> 00:25:00,456
Choose chocolate.
Ui-yeong likes chocolate.

427
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:05,003
I'll get the carrot cake instead, then.

428
00:25:07,255 --> 00:25:08,840
This is for a big group.

429
00:25:09,132 --> 00:25:10,842
The chocolate cake is on the house.

430
00:25:12,468 --> 00:25:14,929
The cake is just for the two of us.

431
00:25:15,763 --> 00:25:17,432
But I won't say no to extra cake.

432
00:25:39,078 --> 00:25:40,288
Hello.

433
00:25:40,455 --> 00:25:41,622
- Mr. Song!
- Hello.

434
00:25:41,706 --> 00:25:43,166
Hello!

435
00:25:43,249 --> 00:25:45,501
You even brought us cake!

436
00:25:45,585 --> 00:25:47,795
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

437
00:25:50,089 --> 00:25:51,924
Why don't we head right up?

438
00:25:52,008 --> 00:25:53,217
Oh, sure.

439
00:25:53,968 --> 00:25:55,011
I'll be back.

440
00:25:55,219 --> 00:25:57,221
Okay. Bye!

441
00:26:39,472 --> 00:26:41,099
Is something wrong?

442
00:26:42,266 --> 00:26:44,018
I'm in a bit of a pickle.

443
00:26:44,602 --> 00:26:47,563
I think talking to you might help.

444
00:26:47,647 --> 00:26:49,232
Oh, sure. What is it?

445
00:26:52,068 --> 00:26:54,278
There's not much space for your pieces.

446
00:26:54,362 --> 00:26:56,614
No, we're trying to come up
with different ideas

447
00:26:56,697 --> 00:26:58,366
but nothing's perfect for the suite.

448
00:26:59,867 --> 00:27:01,160
What can we do?

449
00:27:01,661 --> 00:27:04,163
Let's run a simulation, then.

450
00:27:06,666 --> 00:27:09,585
Okay, I've checked in, and I'm walking in.

451
00:27:09,961 --> 00:27:12,797
I'm looking around the room,
and taking a photo first.

452
00:27:13,464 --> 00:27:15,842
Maybe a selfie. Then

453
00:27:16,801 --> 00:27:17,927
I'll go...

454
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:20,555
- right to the bed!
- What?

455
00:27:21,889 --> 00:27:24,475
I'll roll around this way

456
00:27:25,017 --> 00:27:26,853
and that way.

457
00:27:27,019 --> 00:27:28,604
I'll become one with the bed.

458
00:27:28,688 --> 00:27:30,106
I'll even watch TV from here.

459
00:27:30,189 --> 00:27:32,191
Oh, you're that type.

460
00:27:32,400 --> 00:27:35,319
Then, I only get up

461
00:27:35,570 --> 00:27:36,696
when I'm hungry.

462
00:27:39,949 --> 00:27:42,743
Tae-seop, how about we incorporate the bed
into the design?

463
00:27:42,827 --> 00:27:44,328
- Incorporate the bed?
- Yeah.

464
00:27:44,412 --> 00:27:45,788
Maybe a tray?

465
00:27:45,872 --> 00:27:47,582
You can use that in bed.

466
00:27:47,748 --> 00:27:48,958
Oh.

467
00:27:50,501 --> 00:27:51,502
Oh!

468
00:27:55,923 --> 00:27:57,800
- How about a tray table?
- A tray table?

469
00:27:58,676 --> 00:28:00,469
I used to have this set up on my bed

470
00:28:00,553 --> 00:28:03,097
and ate food on it and even drew pictures.

471
00:28:03,181 --> 00:28:04,223
I see.

472
00:28:05,433 --> 00:28:06,976
That sounds like a great idea.

473
00:28:07,226 --> 00:28:08,936
It won't take up too much space

474
00:28:09,020 --> 00:28:10,771
and it'll go well with whiskey.

475
00:28:10,855 --> 00:28:11,898
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

476
00:28:12,565 --> 00:28:16,736
We should choose a dark shade
for the comforter

477
00:28:16,819 --> 00:28:19,280
so that stains don't show
if anyone spills anything.

478
00:28:22,033 --> 00:28:24,869
I'll work with the tray table idea
and design something.

479
00:28:25,536 --> 00:28:27,079
- Here.
- Yes!

480
00:28:47,934 --> 00:28:48,976
Eui-yeong.

481
00:28:53,189 --> 00:28:54,273
Is she not here?

482
00:28:56,609 --> 00:28:59,487
I thought she was showing him the suite.
Where is she?

483
00:29:01,489 --> 00:29:02,865
Eui-yeong?

484
00:29:05,409 --> 00:29:06,911
Is she in a different suite?

485
00:29:08,537 --> 00:29:09,705
Gosh.

486
00:29:33,521 --> 00:29:34,855
You're off soon, right?

487
00:29:35,815 --> 00:29:36,816
Yeah.

488
00:29:36,899 --> 00:29:38,484
I'll drive you home.

489
00:29:49,662 --> 00:29:50,788
SEASONS OF US

490
00:29:50,871 --> 00:29:52,623
"Seasons of Us" must be back in theaters!

491
00:29:52,915 --> 00:29:55,543
"Seasons of Us"? Is it good?

492
00:29:56,836 --> 00:29:59,588
You haven't watched it?
It got 10 million views!

493
00:30:00,256 --> 00:30:03,050
I watched it three times
because I love that actress.

494
00:30:03,217 --> 00:30:04,760
I see.

495
00:30:04,969 --> 00:30:06,345
I should check it out for sure.

496
00:30:06,637 --> 00:30:08,180
- Tae-seop.
- Yeah?

497
00:30:08,264 --> 00:30:10,099
We got our idea today

498
00:30:10,182 --> 00:30:14,270
so we're done with all the big tasks,
aside from setting up the pop-up.

499
00:30:15,229 --> 00:30:16,230
Yeah?

500
00:30:16,522 --> 00:30:20,651
You want to watch a movie that night
maybe after we set it up?

501
00:30:22,111 --> 00:30:23,988
That movie's really good.

502
00:30:24,155 --> 00:30:27,074
It'd be a shame to miss it again.

503
00:30:27,867 --> 00:30:30,494
Sure, let's get a nice dinner
before that, too.

504
00:30:30,828 --> 00:30:31,996
What's your favorite food?

505
00:30:32,163 --> 00:30:33,289
- I like...
- Yeah?

506
00:30:33,831 --> 00:30:35,916
pretty much everything.
I'm not picky at all.

507
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:39,628
It's going to be so much fun.

508
00:30:49,680 --> 00:30:51,140
Did you just get off work?

509
00:30:52,183 --> 00:30:54,101
- You must've had a long day...
- Whatever.

510
00:30:54,435 --> 00:30:56,562
This is your last chance.
Think before you speak.

511
00:30:56,771 --> 00:30:59,732
I'm sorry for not understanding you.

512
00:30:59,815 --> 00:31:01,942
I'm just very inexperienced in this field.

513
00:31:07,323 --> 00:31:08,491
Is this enough?

514
00:31:15,414 --> 00:31:17,291
You bastard.

515
00:31:19,126 --> 00:31:22,630
I told you it was your last chance,
didn't I?

516
00:31:24,256 --> 00:31:26,384
Didn't I tell you?

517
00:31:26,467 --> 00:31:28,386
- Did I not?
- Wait! Let's talk it out!

518
00:31:28,469 --> 00:31:29,845
- You jerk!
- Use your words!

519
00:31:29,929 --> 00:31:32,264
- It's not that expensive!
- What?

520
00:31:33,724 --> 00:31:37,311
Who are you to decide how much I am?

521
00:31:41,857 --> 00:31:42,858
Hold up.

522
00:31:43,567 --> 00:31:45,277
Decide how much what is?

523
00:31:49,949 --> 00:31:52,701
I didn't know that was for the torn book.

524
00:31:53,869 --> 00:31:55,413
I had no idea.

525
00:31:55,955 --> 00:31:57,665
What do you take me for?

526
00:32:01,419 --> 00:32:03,671
I'm a personal trainer.
I don't eat fried food.

527
00:32:04,713 --> 00:32:06,298
This body took a lot of work.

528
00:32:06,382 --> 00:32:08,509
Sure, you need to protect your gains.

529
00:32:08,592 --> 00:32:11,512
I'm Jung Hyun-min, 30,
and I work at an office.

530
00:32:11,929 --> 00:32:15,433
Just a question,
why did you clean the house that night?

531
00:32:26,694 --> 00:32:27,778
Wait.

532
00:32:28,279 --> 00:32:30,448
It's even weirder
if only the books are put away.

533
00:32:57,141 --> 00:33:00,644
I thought it'd look weirder
if only the books were put away.

534
00:33:00,728 --> 00:33:03,230
So, I just cleaned it all...

535
00:33:21,707 --> 00:33:23,083
You can eat this, right?

536
00:33:23,417 --> 00:33:27,171
I'm good at stripping, you know?

537
00:33:50,069 --> 00:33:53,197
Do you become uninterested in someone
after you have sex with them?

538
00:33:57,201 --> 00:33:58,494
No!

539
00:33:59,203 --> 00:34:00,329
Gosh.

540
00:34:01,205 --> 00:34:02,248
I'm glad.

541
00:34:02,915 --> 00:34:05,167
I really like you.

542
00:34:05,668 --> 00:34:07,169
What do you think about me?

543
00:34:08,045 --> 00:34:10,339
Are you really asking that
after what's happened?

544
00:34:10,422 --> 00:34:12,591
Yeah, we now know
it was a misunderstanding

545
00:34:12,675 --> 00:34:14,176
and we'll be warmed up soon.

546
00:34:14,385 --> 00:34:16,887
And we can eat fried chicken
without fighting over the legs.

547
00:34:16,971 --> 00:34:19,098
How can it get better than this?

548
00:34:20,432 --> 00:34:22,685
Give me a chance, okay?

549
00:34:45,124 --> 00:34:48,210
Mr. Song, you're coming
to set up the pop-up, right?

550
00:34:48,294 --> 00:34:52,172
MR. SONG, YOU'RE COMING
TO SET UP THE POP-UP, RIGHT?

551
00:34:52,256 --> 00:34:53,841
Yeah, see you soon.

552
00:34:56,176 --> 00:34:57,511
Hey, watch out.

553
00:34:57,886 --> 00:34:59,221
Hey!

554
00:34:59,305 --> 00:35:01,015
- Stop destroying everything.
- Okay.

555
00:35:03,642 --> 00:35:06,186
Why are you wearing a white shirt
on the set-up day?

556
00:35:06,770 --> 00:35:08,772
- No, this is good!
- What?

557
00:35:08,856 --> 00:35:11,567
You know the prof from Hannam-dong
who requested a kids' desk?

558
00:35:11,650 --> 00:35:13,944
He asked if we could move the meeting
to tonight.

559
00:35:14,278 --> 00:35:17,239
But I have to take Sua to the doctor,
so you have to take over.

560
00:35:17,323 --> 00:35:19,658
What? No, I have to be at the hotel.

561
00:35:19,742 --> 00:35:21,327
He's our regular. Make time for him.

562
00:35:21,410 --> 00:35:23,078
It's because of his kid's tutoring.

563
00:35:23,162 --> 00:35:25,247
Delay your dinner plans
until after the meeting.

564
00:35:27,333 --> 00:35:29,376
Tell him to come
as soon as possible, then.

565
00:35:29,877 --> 00:35:30,878
Jin-su!

566
00:35:33,213 --> 00:35:34,757
- Yeah?
- I'll go after the meeting.

567
00:35:34,840 --> 00:35:36,216
Please tell the hotel.

568
00:35:36,300 --> 00:35:37,885
And send me photo updates.

569
00:35:37,968 --> 00:35:39,553
- Photos?
- Yeah.

570
00:35:42,389 --> 00:35:44,725
That intern is like Ui-yeong.

571
00:35:44,850 --> 00:35:46,268
She's a wolf in sheep's clothing.

572
00:35:46,393 --> 00:35:49,730
She looks kind,
but inside, she's real picky.

573
00:35:51,023 --> 00:35:54,902
You're rich with a new car
and an expensive taste for drinks now.

574
00:35:55,486 --> 00:35:57,529
How come your taste in women
hasn't changed?

575
00:35:58,197 --> 00:35:59,406
You think so?

576
00:36:00,407 --> 00:36:02,785
Stop wasting time on someone
who won't give you a chance.

577
00:36:03,494 --> 00:36:05,245
I have ladies lined up to meet you.

578
00:36:05,329 --> 00:36:07,665
You sure you don't want to return
to the law firm?

579
00:36:20,803 --> 00:36:23,847
Okay, let's go! One, two, three.

580
00:36:31,188 --> 00:36:32,606
- Hello.
- Hi.

581
00:36:32,731 --> 00:36:34,608
Did Mr. Song come with you?

582
00:36:34,692 --> 00:36:36,944
Oh, he couldn't make it.
He had a client meeting.

583
00:36:37,027 --> 00:36:38,195
Did he not tell you?

584
00:36:38,278 --> 00:36:40,197
Oh, maybe.

585
00:36:41,907 --> 00:36:43,826
- No, he didn't.
- He must've forgotten.

586
00:36:43,909 --> 00:36:45,077
He forgets all the time.

587
00:36:45,369 --> 00:36:46,370
I see.

588
00:36:49,456 --> 00:36:51,834
Which floor should we take these to?

589
00:36:51,917 --> 00:36:54,712
All of this is for the lobby.
This way, please.

590
00:36:59,925 --> 00:37:00,968
Be careful.

591
00:37:02,261 --> 00:37:03,262
Take your time.

592
00:37:06,306 --> 00:37:07,683
- There? Okay.
- Yeah.

593
00:37:13,063 --> 00:37:14,815
You can just help with the lighter stuff.

594
00:37:15,107 --> 00:37:17,484
I guess I was a little too ambitious.

595
00:37:17,735 --> 00:37:18,986
- Let me help.
- Okay.

596
00:37:19,069 --> 00:37:21,655
- This is heavier than I thought.
- Yeah.

597
00:37:22,823 --> 00:37:23,824
This way.

598
00:37:24,992 --> 00:37:27,619
So, she has no issues
receiving help from anyone else.

599
00:37:28,287 --> 00:37:30,539
- See you tomorrow at 6 p.m.
- Okay!

600
00:37:34,418 --> 00:37:36,503
- Hello.
- Hello.

601
00:37:36,670 --> 00:37:38,255
- Ready to order?
- Yeah.

602
00:37:39,506 --> 00:37:42,593
I'll take 10 iced Americano, hot.

603
00:37:42,676 --> 00:37:44,386
I'll also take another 10, cold.

604
00:37:44,470 --> 00:37:47,681
And one hot chocolate.

605
00:37:48,640 --> 00:37:50,017
And I'll take all the desserts.

606
00:37:50,642 --> 00:37:52,519
- All the desserts?
- Yeah.

607
00:37:53,145 --> 00:37:54,188
Ji-su!

608
00:38:02,946 --> 00:38:05,073
- Come again.
- Goodnight.

609
00:38:10,871 --> 00:38:12,164
Sir

610
00:38:12,372 --> 00:38:13,916
are you going somewhere close?

611
00:38:13,999 --> 00:38:16,668
Yeah, The Hills Hotel.

612
00:38:16,752 --> 00:38:18,879
My crush is working late today.

613
00:38:19,254 --> 00:38:21,673
Oh, the hotel?

614
00:38:33,852 --> 00:38:35,521
You can just put them here.

615
00:38:35,604 --> 00:38:36,605
Oh, sure.

616
00:38:38,065 --> 00:38:39,399
Alright, then.

617
00:38:40,275 --> 00:38:41,568
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

618
00:38:46,698 --> 00:38:47,950
Oh? Why are you here?

619
00:38:48,367 --> 00:38:50,536
- Just making a delivery.
- You deliver?

620
00:38:50,869 --> 00:38:53,121
Just for the day. You? Working late?

621
00:38:53,205 --> 00:38:55,207
Oh, it's for the event
I mentioned last time.

622
00:38:55,290 --> 00:38:58,085
Everyone, have some coffee!

623
00:38:58,168 --> 00:39:00,003
- Do-hyun?
- Have some coffee.

624
00:39:00,087 --> 00:39:01,880
Sae-byeok! Over here.

625
00:39:02,631 --> 00:39:03,757
Mr. Kang?

626
00:39:04,508 --> 00:39:06,051
What are you doing here?

627
00:39:06,760 --> 00:39:10,889
I got coffee for everyone
because you were working late.

628
00:39:10,973 --> 00:39:13,559
But I got you hot chocolate
because it's nighttime.

629
00:39:13,642 --> 00:39:15,644
Wait. Let me see which one it is.

630
00:39:15,727 --> 00:39:17,604
- Just a sec!
- I'm fine...

631
00:39:18,397 --> 00:39:21,817
Why didn't the barista label them?

632
00:39:23,902 --> 00:39:26,446
Did I ever ask you

633
00:39:26,738 --> 00:39:28,782
to do this for me?

634
00:39:29,366 --> 00:39:30,617
No, right?

635
00:39:30,701 --> 00:39:31,910
I'll be right back.

636
00:39:35,372 --> 00:39:36,415
Do-hyun.

637
00:39:36,748 --> 00:39:38,083
Talk to her tomorrow.

638
00:39:38,166 --> 00:39:40,419
Our partnering company is here, too.

639
00:39:40,502 --> 00:39:43,338
Can't I at least get you coffee?

640
00:39:43,672 --> 00:39:46,383
If she feels uncomfortable about it

641
00:39:46,925 --> 00:39:48,635
you need to give her space.

642
00:39:48,719 --> 00:39:50,971
You're responsible for this, too.

643
00:39:51,471 --> 00:39:53,724
- What?
- Don't you owe me an apology?

644
00:39:54,266 --> 00:39:56,101
For what?

645
00:39:57,144 --> 00:40:01,189
Sae-byeok would've taken me seriously

646
00:40:01,273 --> 00:40:03,859
if it weren't for you.

647
00:40:05,110 --> 00:40:06,111
Why...

648
00:40:08,196 --> 00:40:14,036
Why did you suddenly decide
that you liked me and get in my way?

649
00:40:15,037 --> 00:40:16,079
Oh, I...

650
00:40:17,539 --> 00:40:18,624
This is...

651
00:40:25,756 --> 00:40:26,798
Bye.

652
00:40:27,925 --> 00:40:30,177
I'll take these back.

653
00:40:33,013 --> 00:40:34,139
Wait!

654
00:40:37,142 --> 00:40:38,226
Oh, no!

655
00:40:40,729 --> 00:40:41,772
Are you okay?

656
00:40:42,773 --> 00:40:44,858
- It burns!
- I'll take you to the hospital.

657
00:40:48,487 --> 00:40:49,821
Bring something to wipe it with.

658
00:40:50,280 --> 00:40:51,782
Gosh, what do we do?

659
00:40:54,826 --> 00:40:56,036
Mr. Kang.

660
00:40:57,371 --> 00:41:00,791
You seem to be badly mistaken

661
00:41:00,874 --> 00:41:02,709
but this isn't about Ui-yeong.

662
00:41:02,793 --> 00:41:04,169
People like you

663
00:41:05,087 --> 00:41:07,714
who think their feelings are
the only ones that matter

664
00:41:08,632 --> 00:41:11,802
make me feel so uncomfortable.

665
00:41:13,261 --> 00:41:14,513
You make me uncomfortable.

666
00:41:14,805 --> 00:41:15,847
No, I can't stand you.

667
00:41:15,931 --> 00:41:17,808
Not even as a friend or a coworker.

668
00:41:17,891 --> 00:41:19,810
So, please

669
00:41:21,144 --> 00:41:22,479
stop trying to win me over.

670
00:41:29,444 --> 00:41:31,405
Put that back up, too!

671
00:41:39,830 --> 00:41:40,956
Jin-su

672
00:41:41,498 --> 00:41:43,542
- call Mr. Song.
- Okay.

673
00:41:51,758 --> 00:41:54,261
Sorry, I'm late. Something came up,
but I'm on my way now.

674
00:42:05,689 --> 00:42:07,482
THERE'S BEEN A BIG ACCIDENT

675
00:42:07,566 --> 00:42:08,817
There's been a big accident.

676
00:42:09,568 --> 00:42:10,777
We need you to come here.

677
00:42:12,487 --> 00:42:13,655
What happened?

678
00:42:17,159 --> 00:42:19,036
Thankfully, it's not a big burn.

679
00:42:19,119 --> 00:42:20,787
Okay, thank you.

680
00:42:26,251 --> 00:42:27,502
- Here's the receipt.
- Okay.

681
00:42:43,727 --> 00:42:46,438
Don't you know you have to make sure
not even water touches them?

682
00:42:47,105 --> 00:42:49,316
I'm sorry. It's my fault.

683
00:42:49,399 --> 00:42:52,069
Your employees did nothing but work hard.

684
00:42:52,319 --> 00:42:54,071
No, it's not your fault.

685
00:42:54,154 --> 00:42:55,864
There was a bit of an accident.

686
00:42:57,157 --> 00:42:59,242
Let's use a dark oil
to finish the surface again.

687
00:42:59,659 --> 00:43:00,827
For all the pieces?

688
00:43:00,911 --> 00:43:02,204
Yeah, to match the colors.

689
00:43:02,287 --> 00:43:03,872
Hurry. Let's get it done tonight.

690
00:43:04,039 --> 00:43:05,082
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

691
00:43:34,653 --> 00:43:37,030
Roll it on like this.

692
00:43:41,159 --> 00:43:42,244
Oh, I...

693
00:43:42,577 --> 00:43:45,163
I'll have to return to the hotel.

694
00:43:45,247 --> 00:43:47,249
With that hand? You sure?

695
00:43:48,333 --> 00:43:51,002
I think I left my phone at the hotel

696
00:43:51,086 --> 00:43:53,338
and everyone must be busy
fixing the furniture.

697
00:43:53,421 --> 00:43:54,881
I need to check on them.

698
00:44:00,178 --> 00:44:01,388
Call them and ask first.

699
00:44:01,471 --> 00:44:03,098
Oh, okay.

700
00:44:11,606 --> 00:44:12,774
Is this dark enough?

701
00:44:13,191 --> 00:44:15,152
Go over this area again.

702
00:44:15,735 --> 00:44:19,072
Mr. Song is here to take care of it.

703
00:44:19,406 --> 00:44:21,158
Oh, he came.

704
00:44:21,241 --> 00:44:22,951
Yeah, it's almost done

705
00:44:23,034 --> 00:44:25,203
so don't come to the hotel.
Go home and rest.

706
00:44:25,287 --> 00:44:28,039
It must've really hurt. I'm so sorry.

707
00:44:28,248 --> 00:44:29,624
You don't need to apologize.

708
00:44:31,668 --> 00:44:34,796
I'll just go home, then. See you tomorrow.

709
00:44:34,880 --> 00:44:36,381
Okay, see you tomorrow.

710
00:44:36,464 --> 00:44:37,465
Okay.

711
00:44:40,635 --> 00:44:41,761
Let's go home.

712
00:44:43,013 --> 00:44:45,473
But there's a place we have to go
before that.

713
00:44:46,391 --> 00:44:49,394
Oh, I was too shocked to ask earlier

714
00:44:49,477 --> 00:44:50,979
but why do you have two helmets?

715
00:44:51,062 --> 00:44:52,314
One for you, and one for me.

716
00:44:52,397 --> 00:44:54,274
You said you wanted a ride one day.

717
00:45:10,916 --> 00:45:12,459
This is so refreshing.

718
00:45:13,251 --> 00:45:14,252
What?

719
00:45:14,628 --> 00:45:16,129
It's so refreshing!

720
00:45:18,381 --> 00:45:20,258
I feel so refreshed now!

721
00:45:32,103 --> 00:45:34,064
Ms. Lee tried to stop him

722
00:45:34,147 --> 00:45:38,443
and he started blaming her for everything
in front of everyone.

723
00:45:38,526 --> 00:45:40,028
What does this mean?

724
00:45:40,946 --> 00:45:42,280
A love triangle.

725
00:45:42,656 --> 00:45:43,990
There's no way.

726
00:45:44,366 --> 00:45:47,452
Think about it. Mr. Kang likes Ms. Sim

727
00:45:47,535 --> 00:45:48,787
and Ms. Lee is in his way.

728
00:45:48,870 --> 00:45:50,705
That means they either dated
or had a fling.

729
00:45:51,498 --> 00:45:53,792
You know nothing. You've never even dated.

730
00:45:53,875 --> 00:45:56,253
Even so, I can tell
they don't look good together.

731
00:45:56,962 --> 00:45:59,339
Over there. That's the lawyer.

732
00:46:05,804 --> 00:46:06,805
Just a sec.

733
00:46:16,648 --> 00:46:18,942
Are you Mr. Song Tae-seop?

734
00:46:19,025 --> 00:46:20,193
Mr. Kang?

735
00:46:21,069 --> 00:46:22,654
Do you have a minute to talk?

736
00:46:25,824 --> 00:46:27,492
What do you want to say?

737
00:46:29,411 --> 00:46:32,414
If it's about the furniture,
it was something out of my control...

738
00:46:32,497 --> 00:46:35,000
Yeah, I'm mad about that,
but that's being taken care of.

739
00:46:35,250 --> 00:46:37,919
And if things go wrong,
I can ask the hotel for compensation

740
00:46:38,003 --> 00:46:39,963
since it's very clear who's at fault.

741
00:46:40,630 --> 00:46:43,091
You wrote the contract,
so you must know what's in it.

742
00:46:44,718 --> 00:46:46,469
Are you blackmailing me?

743
00:46:46,553 --> 00:46:49,431
That's a violation of Article 283...

744
00:46:49,514 --> 00:46:52,475
Not sure if this is blackmailing

745
00:46:53,476 --> 00:46:55,103
but I like Ui-yeong.

746
00:46:56,354 --> 00:46:58,732
- What?
- She's important to me

747
00:46:59,065 --> 00:47:00,567
so please watch your mouth.

748
00:47:03,570 --> 00:47:05,655
So, this is about Ui-yeong?

749
00:47:05,739 --> 00:47:07,824
Watch your words, actions, and thoughts.

750
00:47:08,575 --> 00:47:09,909
All of them.

751
00:47:32,807 --> 00:47:35,101
SORRY, I'M LATE. SOMETHING CAME UP,
BUT I'M ON MY WAY NOW.

752
00:47:49,574 --> 00:47:52,327
SONG TAE-SEOP

753
00:47:52,410 --> 00:47:53,453
Huh?

754
00:47:57,499 --> 00:47:59,459
SONG TAE-SEOP, EUI-YEONG

755
00:48:13,640 --> 00:48:15,225
Man, what is this?

756
00:48:15,892 --> 00:48:17,602
Isn't it just ordinary ramyeon?

757
00:48:18,103 --> 00:48:19,229
Why is it so good?

758
00:48:19,729 --> 00:48:21,815
Because the view is extraordinary.

759
00:48:21,898 --> 00:48:24,192
Doesn't it just soothe your soul?

760
00:48:33,910 --> 00:48:34,994
I'm so full now.

761
00:48:37,038 --> 00:48:39,791
Did you like that lawyer guy, too?

762
00:48:41,793 --> 00:48:42,836
Do you fall that easily?

763
00:48:43,044 --> 00:48:45,964
It's not like that. He was just...

764
00:48:46,381 --> 00:48:47,674
a quick crush.

765
00:48:47,966 --> 00:48:50,301
You have a horrible taste in men.

766
00:48:50,844 --> 00:48:53,179
Don't trust the guy you kissed, either.

767
00:48:53,388 --> 00:48:55,974
Where is he
when your hand is all bandaged?

768
00:48:57,016 --> 00:48:59,269
He's the CEO. He must be busy.

769
00:49:00,353 --> 00:49:02,439
You must be tired, too.

770
00:49:02,730 --> 00:49:04,315
You worked all day, right?

771
00:49:04,816 --> 00:49:06,860
Is working at the cafe okay?

772
00:49:06,943 --> 00:49:10,405
I'm sure you can make more money
in movies or dramas.

773
00:49:11,197 --> 00:49:13,408
I don't want to chase money with acting.

774
00:49:13,825 --> 00:49:15,076
I do it out of love.

775
00:49:15,160 --> 00:49:18,246
Yeah. You can do what you love
and earn money.

776
00:49:18,455 --> 00:49:20,331
And wouldn't it be nice to get famous?

777
00:49:20,415 --> 00:49:21,875
But there will be consequences.

778
00:49:21,958 --> 00:49:24,627
I'd have to give up moments like this.

779
00:49:24,752 --> 00:49:25,837
I see.

780
00:49:26,838 --> 00:49:30,216
This view soothes me...

781
00:49:32,260 --> 00:49:33,678
more than any fame or money.

782
00:49:34,471 --> 00:49:35,597
I see.

783
00:49:44,522 --> 00:49:45,523
Thank you.

784
00:49:46,399 --> 00:49:48,151
- Here.
- Thanks.

785
00:49:48,318 --> 00:49:49,819
Thanks for working until so late.

786
00:49:49,903 --> 00:49:53,364
It was nothing.
Thanks so much for your help.

787
00:49:53,823 --> 00:49:55,617
Oh, this...

788
00:49:56,117 --> 00:49:58,119
What was that?

789
00:49:59,746 --> 00:50:00,747
It's nothing.

790
00:50:00,872 --> 00:50:04,000
Your arms and shoulders will be sore.
Give yourself a good massage.

791
00:50:04,083 --> 00:50:06,294
Okay, thanks for all your help.

792
00:50:06,377 --> 00:50:07,587
- Good work.
- Thanks.

793
00:50:45,291 --> 00:50:46,834
They say tears take away sadness.

794
00:50:46,918 --> 00:50:48,419
Does the wind take away anger?

795
00:50:48,586 --> 00:50:50,421
All my anger's gone with the wind.

796
00:50:50,505 --> 00:50:52,006
Call me when you want to cruise.

797
00:50:52,090 --> 00:50:54,300
And you know,
I make cocktails at the cafe at night.

798
00:50:55,009 --> 00:50:57,303
Visit me. I'll give you freebies.

799
00:50:57,720 --> 00:50:59,013
Here. Give me your number.

800
00:51:13,653 --> 00:51:14,654
Huh?

801
00:51:16,447 --> 00:51:18,658
What brings you here?

802
00:51:18,741 --> 00:51:20,326
You left your phone at the hotel.

803
00:51:20,827 --> 00:51:24,205
Oh, I was going to get it tomorrow.
Thanks.

804
00:51:24,289 --> 00:51:26,833
Can we talk? Just for a sec.

805
00:51:26,916 --> 00:51:28,001
Oh...

806
00:51:28,960 --> 00:51:31,754
I'll talk to him and head in.
You can go first.

807
00:51:32,088 --> 00:51:33,715
- Thanks for today.
- Sure.

808
00:51:37,719 --> 00:51:39,345
What happened to your arm?

809
00:51:39,429 --> 00:51:41,055
Did you see a doctor about it?

810
00:51:41,139 --> 00:51:45,059
I got a burn from the coffee spill,
but it's nothing bad.

811
00:51:46,269 --> 00:51:50,273
Sae-byeok told me
you sorted things out at the hotel.

812
00:51:50,356 --> 00:51:51,399
Thank you.

813
00:51:51,566 --> 00:51:54,694
This wouldn't have happened
if I'd just come sooner.

814
00:51:55,653 --> 00:51:57,196
But you couldn't.

815
00:52:00,158 --> 00:52:01,242
You know

816
00:52:02,744 --> 00:52:06,039
I was waiting for you.

817
00:52:07,665 --> 00:52:08,750
Sorry.

818
00:52:09,167 --> 00:52:10,877
I won't be late

819
00:52:11,878 --> 00:52:13,379
or make you wait again.

820
00:52:17,425 --> 00:52:20,386
Do you have any photos of the pop-up?

821
00:52:20,470 --> 00:52:22,889
- You want to see some?
- Yeah.

822
00:52:24,766 --> 00:52:26,893
- Here.
- Wow!

823
00:52:28,061 --> 00:52:30,313
That's even better than what I imagined.

824
00:52:30,730 --> 00:52:31,731
It's nice, right?

825
00:52:41,908 --> 00:52:43,493
I got home safely.

826
00:52:43,743 --> 00:52:44,911
Rest well.

827
00:52:54,712 --> 00:52:56,464
- Hyun-min, is everything ready?
- What?

828
00:52:56,547 --> 00:52:57,882
Yeah, I think so.

829
00:52:58,883 --> 00:53:00,093
- Ui-yeong!
- Hey.

830
00:53:00,176 --> 00:53:02,845
The bartender we hired just called

831
00:53:02,929 --> 00:53:04,764
and he can't come. His family is unwell.

832
00:53:04,847 --> 00:53:06,849
- What?
- On the day of the event?

833
00:53:06,933 --> 00:53:07,975
Yeah...

834
00:53:08,059 --> 00:53:10,478
But we have to have a bartender!

835
00:53:10,561 --> 00:53:11,729
What should we do?

836
00:53:11,896 --> 00:53:14,315
Oh, wait. I can fix this.

837
00:53:16,693 --> 00:53:20,113
The pieces you made are perfect
for our hotel.

838
00:53:20,571 --> 00:53:23,449
This octagon tray table is my favorite.

839
00:53:23,533 --> 00:53:24,575
Thanks.

840
00:53:25,159 --> 00:53:29,914
I heard you came up
with the tray table idea with Ms. Song.

841
00:53:29,997 --> 00:53:32,208
You two have great teamwork.

842
00:53:32,291 --> 00:53:33,334
Thank you.

843
00:53:34,210 --> 00:53:35,628
And the suites will be opened

844
00:53:35,712 --> 00:53:39,465
to the brand reps and VIP guests
as a tester first

845
00:53:39,841 --> 00:53:43,428
fixed as needed,
then be open to all guests.

846
00:53:43,553 --> 00:53:46,597
And we'll collect all orders
from the pop-up on a list

847
00:53:46,681 --> 00:53:48,266
and have Ui-yeong send it to you.

848
00:53:48,349 --> 00:53:49,976
- Okay, thank you.
- Thanks.

849
00:53:52,270 --> 00:53:53,438
And here.

850
00:53:53,980 --> 00:53:57,150
This is a small gift
for all of your team's hard work.

851
00:53:57,233 --> 00:53:58,693
- My gosh.
- Wow!

852
00:53:59,110 --> 00:54:00,528
They're going to be so happy.

853
00:54:00,611 --> 00:54:01,612
Yeah.

854
00:54:01,696 --> 00:54:03,322
This room is for you, Mr. Song.

855
00:54:03,406 --> 00:54:06,409
You can rest up until I call you
in time for the pop-up event.

856
00:54:06,492 --> 00:54:08,369
- Okay, thank you.
- See you.

857
00:54:17,336 --> 00:54:20,131
I couldn't find anything else,
so I just got our uniform and a tie.

858
00:54:20,214 --> 00:54:22,550
Yeah? It's okay, there's nothing else.

859
00:54:22,633 --> 00:54:24,385
- We did our best.
- Yeah.

860
00:54:28,306 --> 00:54:29,640
How do I look?

861
00:54:30,683 --> 00:54:31,809
Are the sleeves too short?

862
00:54:53,664 --> 00:54:57,043
We've hired a bartender
to make the drinks for tonight.

863
00:54:57,126 --> 00:54:58,377
That's amazing.

864
00:54:59,587 --> 00:55:01,297
If you buy one or two bottles...

865
00:55:01,547 --> 00:55:02,924
As you can see...

866
00:55:03,007 --> 00:55:04,008
DEERFIDDICH

867
00:55:15,645 --> 00:55:16,729
Here you go.

868
00:55:31,244 --> 00:55:32,245
Hey!

869
00:55:35,623 --> 00:55:37,041
My wrists are dying.

870
00:55:37,124 --> 00:55:38,876
I said I'd make cocktails for you.

871
00:55:39,168 --> 00:55:41,170
When did I say I'd make some for everyone?

872
00:55:41,921 --> 00:55:43,464
I promise to repay you for it.

873
00:55:43,548 --> 00:55:47,176
Did that Tae-seop guy
really build all this?

874
00:55:47,260 --> 00:55:48,803
Yeah, impressive, right?

875
00:55:50,972 --> 00:55:52,557
Oh? Tae-seop!

876
00:55:52,890 --> 00:55:53,933
Hey, Ui-yeong.

877
00:55:56,060 --> 00:55:57,228
You want a drink?

878
00:55:57,311 --> 00:55:58,563
No, I'm fine.

879
00:55:58,855 --> 00:55:59,897
Have you looked around?

880
00:55:59,981 --> 00:56:01,399
Yeah, it looks incredible.

881
00:56:01,524 --> 00:56:04,861
And the brand reps seem very satisfied.

882
00:56:04,944 --> 00:56:06,153
I'm so glad.

883
00:56:06,654 --> 00:56:08,906
- If you have time...
- Mr. Song!

884
00:56:09,031 --> 00:56:10,449
Could you say hi to those guests?

885
00:56:10,533 --> 00:56:11,784
Oh, sure.

886
00:56:11,868 --> 00:56:12,869
- Just a sec.
- Okay.

887
00:56:17,832 --> 00:56:19,458
Look, it's Son Jeong-a!

888
00:56:20,126 --> 00:56:21,502
What's she doing here?

889
00:56:21,586 --> 00:56:25,798
The brand is the main sponsor
for the Geumsang Arts Awards.

890
00:56:26,090 --> 00:56:28,759
This is unbelievable. She's stunning!

891
00:56:28,926 --> 00:56:30,761
She's my favorite actress.

892
00:56:30,887 --> 00:56:33,556
How's she an actress?
She doesn't even act anymore.

893
00:56:34,140 --> 00:56:35,433
She's just an influencer now.

894
00:56:38,060 --> 00:56:39,562
Did you see that? She winked at me!

895
00:56:42,565 --> 00:56:44,191
You saw her winking at me, right?

896
00:56:44,442 --> 00:56:45,443
Hi!

897
00:57:18,809 --> 00:57:20,603
- Here you are.
- Yeah.

898
00:57:20,686 --> 00:57:23,898
You seem busy,
introducing yourself to everyone.

899
00:57:23,981 --> 00:57:25,066
I know.

900
00:57:25,149 --> 00:57:27,109
But I think I'm good for now.

901
00:57:27,193 --> 00:57:29,612
Yeah, everything went well,
all thanks to you.

902
00:58:01,227 --> 00:58:03,312
- Ui-yeong.
- Yeah?

903
00:58:03,521 --> 00:58:05,940
About what we couldn't do last time.
Are you free today...

904
00:58:06,023 --> 00:58:07,441
- Ms. Lee!
- Yes!

905
00:58:07,525 --> 00:58:10,569
Some people don't seem to know
about the afterparty today.

906
00:58:10,653 --> 00:58:12,154
You sure you announced it?

907
00:58:12,613 --> 00:58:14,615
- Oh, right.
- Come on.

908
00:58:15,992 --> 00:58:17,159
What about you?

909
00:58:17,702 --> 00:58:19,620
Oh, I don't drink, so...

910
00:58:19,704 --> 00:58:24,333
We're going to the cafe by the hotel.
Please join us with your team.

911
00:58:25,376 --> 00:58:28,838
I don't drink,
but I always attend afterparties.

912
00:58:28,921 --> 00:58:31,173
That's a proper way to finish a project,
after all.

913
00:58:31,257 --> 00:58:33,217
- Join us, then.
- Okay, see you later.

914
00:58:33,300 --> 00:58:34,552
You promised!

915
00:58:44,895 --> 00:58:45,938
That was great.

916
00:58:46,022 --> 00:58:48,190
- Great work.
- You, too.

917
00:58:48,482 --> 00:58:50,067
- Hello.
- Hello.

918
00:58:50,151 --> 00:58:51,944
- Good work.
- You, too.

919
00:58:52,028 --> 00:58:53,404
- This way!
- Hi!

920
00:58:53,487 --> 00:58:54,822
- Have a seat.
- Great work!

921
00:58:54,905 --> 00:58:56,157
- Welcome!
- Good job.

922
00:58:56,240 --> 00:58:57,908
- Have a seat.
- Come.

923
00:58:57,992 --> 00:58:58,993
Okay.

924
00:58:59,201 --> 00:59:01,871
How are you everywhere?

925
00:59:01,954 --> 00:59:03,539
I'm where I'm supposed to be.

926
00:59:04,081 --> 00:59:07,001
Have you maybe considered
that you're the one intruding?

927
00:59:07,084 --> 00:59:09,754
I work for these afterparties.

928
00:59:10,463 --> 00:59:12,339
You can sit there.

929
00:59:12,423 --> 00:59:13,966
Mr. Song!

930
00:59:14,175 --> 00:59:16,177
- This way.
- No...

931
00:59:16,260 --> 00:59:19,013
I already saved a seat for you.
Have a drink.

932
00:59:19,096 --> 00:59:21,057
- No, I...
- Join me first.

933
00:59:21,140 --> 00:59:23,350
- Sit with them later.
- Great work today.

934
00:59:23,434 --> 00:59:24,769
You, too.

935
00:59:24,852 --> 00:59:27,563
- Come on.
- Where's Mr. Lee?

936
00:59:27,646 --> 00:59:29,899
He couldn't make it.
He had to watch his daughter.

937
00:59:29,982 --> 00:59:32,568
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

938
00:59:32,651 --> 00:59:33,986
Alright.

939
00:59:35,279 --> 00:59:38,240
- So, you want a glass?
- No, I don't drink.

940
00:59:38,324 --> 00:59:40,409
Okay, just fill it
for the sake of raising it.

941
00:59:40,618 --> 00:59:42,078
Here comes your drink

942
00:59:42,161 --> 00:59:44,747
- Chug!
- Thank you

943
00:59:44,830 --> 00:59:46,457
Ji-su, join us.

944
00:59:46,540 --> 00:59:47,833
- Can you?
- Come here.

945
00:59:47,917 --> 00:59:49,001
Alright.

946
00:59:50,086 --> 00:59:51,670
A glass for you, Na-ri.

947
00:59:51,754 --> 00:59:53,506
We need to drink on a day like this.

948
00:59:53,589 --> 00:59:54,840
Let's see...

949
00:59:55,966 --> 00:59:57,635
- I'll pour for you.
- Okay.

950
00:59:59,637 --> 01:00:01,514
- Good work.
- You, too.

951
01:00:01,972 --> 01:00:04,058
Everyone, fill your glasses!

952
01:00:04,141 --> 01:00:08,312
Take good care of yourselves,
and see you again in a new project!

953
01:00:08,395 --> 01:00:10,439
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

954
01:00:10,523 --> 01:00:11,732
- Good work!
- Good work!

955
01:00:11,816 --> 01:00:13,067
- Great job.
- You, too.

956
01:00:13,150 --> 01:00:15,027
- Good work.
- Good work.

957
01:00:21,283 --> 01:00:23,369
Oh, no, the drink tastes sweet.
I'm screwed.

958
01:00:23,452 --> 01:00:24,453
I'm starving.

959
01:00:24,537 --> 01:00:26,789
- What does the bunny say?
- What does the bunny say?

960
01:00:29,041 --> 01:00:31,335
- Bunny!
- Carrot!

961
01:00:31,502 --> 01:00:33,629
Hold up, where's Mr. Kang?

962
01:00:33,921 --> 01:00:35,673
I doubt that he's coming.

963
01:00:36,006 --> 01:00:37,550
How would you know that?

964
01:00:38,717 --> 01:00:39,885
Just have a drink.

965
01:00:41,095 --> 01:00:43,597
Let's all raise our glasses without her!

966
01:00:43,681 --> 01:00:45,933
- Sounds good!
- Let's go!

967
01:00:46,016 --> 01:00:47,393
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

968
01:00:50,521 --> 01:00:54,150
So, Ji-su, what are you? A bartender?

969
01:00:54,233 --> 01:00:57,611
Oh! He's actually an actor.

970
01:00:58,112 --> 01:00:59,989
- Really?
- No way!

971
01:01:00,072 --> 01:01:04,076
I worked a lot of part-time jobs
while acting on stage, and here I am.

972
01:01:04,368 --> 01:01:05,369
Really?

973
01:01:05,452 --> 01:01:07,997
No wonder you have that aura.

974
01:01:08,455 --> 01:01:10,082
Do you have a fandom?

975
01:01:10,166 --> 01:01:12,376
If not, I'll be the leader.

976
01:01:12,459 --> 01:01:15,796
- My gosh!
- Really?

977
01:01:16,005 --> 01:01:17,673
No, just be my audience.

978
01:01:17,756 --> 01:01:20,968
I'll invite everyone here to my show.
Promise me you'll come.

979
01:01:21,051 --> 01:01:23,387
- Sounds good!
- I'd love that!

980
01:01:23,679 --> 01:01:24,763
Promise me!

981
01:01:24,847 --> 01:01:27,099
- Okay!
- Cheers!

982
01:01:30,936 --> 01:01:32,813
- You have to keep your word.
- Of course.

983
01:01:33,063 --> 01:01:34,190
Oh, not yet.

984
01:01:36,108 --> 01:01:37,985
We have to go!

985
01:01:39,653 --> 01:01:40,905
- Let's go!
- Come on.

986
01:01:40,988 --> 01:01:42,531
Everyone has to come!

987
01:01:43,782 --> 01:01:46,827
- Keep drinking!
- Chug!

988
01:01:46,911 --> 01:01:48,579
Do you drive on the Gangbyeonbuk-ro

989
01:01:48,662 --> 01:01:51,832
if you live in that area?

990
01:01:52,082 --> 01:01:53,751
Do you usually...

991
01:01:54,084 --> 01:01:56,921
Mr. Kang... Where's Mr. Kang?

992
01:02:14,688 --> 01:02:16,815
You can't drink
more than two bottles of soju.

993
01:02:16,899 --> 01:02:19,360
How many fingers am I holding up?

994
01:02:20,486 --> 01:02:24,406
How did you end up with six fingers?

995
01:02:27,576 --> 01:02:28,661
Wait.

996
01:02:29,620 --> 01:02:31,205
I need some fresh air.

997
01:02:34,708 --> 01:02:35,960
Be careful.

998
01:02:39,088 --> 01:02:40,464
I'll be right back.

999
01:02:44,093 --> 01:02:47,054
I...

1000
01:02:54,812 --> 01:02:56,063
Tae-seop.

1001
01:02:56,730 --> 01:02:58,065
Tae-seop?

1002
01:02:58,691 --> 01:03:01,318
Are you okay?

1003
01:03:04,446 --> 01:03:07,199
No, I'm not.

1004
01:03:07,283 --> 01:03:08,742
I feel...

1005
01:03:09,451 --> 01:03:12,579
- like I'm going crazy.
- Oh, no.

1006
01:03:12,913 --> 01:03:16,041
Let me get you a hangover drink.

1007
01:03:16,125 --> 01:03:17,876
Just wait here, okay?

1008
01:03:18,460 --> 01:03:20,254
No, don't leave me.

1009
01:03:21,922 --> 01:03:25,259
- What?
- You're so close to me

1010
01:03:26,635 --> 01:03:30,139
yet I can't reach you.
That drives me crazy.

1011
01:03:42,776 --> 01:03:43,819
You can't go.

1012
01:03:57,249 --> 01:03:59,710
I didn't know you were so cute
when you got drunk.

1013
01:04:07,593 --> 01:04:08,677
Tae-seop.

1014
01:04:09,470 --> 01:04:10,888
I'm not going anywhere.

1015
01:04:11,972 --> 01:04:15,309
You don't have to hold my hand so tight.

1016
01:04:17,603 --> 01:04:18,687
Okay.

1017
01:04:19,313 --> 01:04:20,773
But Ui-yeong

1018
01:04:22,858 --> 01:04:26,487
do you still want to go on a date with me?

1019
01:04:27,529 --> 01:04:28,572
Yeah.

1020
01:04:29,531 --> 01:04:30,741
I do.

1021
01:04:30,991 --> 01:04:32,284
Then...

1022
01:04:34,161 --> 01:04:35,662
you want to go...

1023
01:04:36,914 --> 01:04:38,540
for another drink, just the two of us?

1024
01:04:40,125 --> 01:04:41,543
Right now?

1025
01:04:47,049 --> 01:04:48,092
Sure.

1026
01:04:49,593 --> 01:04:52,471
Let me just grab my purse.

1027
01:04:52,554 --> 01:04:54,890
Stay right here, okay?

1028
01:04:57,518 --> 01:04:59,853
Don't go anywhere. Stay right here, okay?

1029
01:05:00,687 --> 01:05:02,147
I'll be right back!

1030
01:05:27,214 --> 01:05:28,590
Tae-seop!

1031
01:05:30,968 --> 01:05:31,969
Oh?

1032
01:05:32,219 --> 01:05:34,513
You can't sleep here!

1033
01:05:34,596 --> 01:05:36,557
Wake up, Tae-seop.

1034
01:05:36,974 --> 01:05:38,934
It's not safe to sleep out here!

1035
01:05:40,561 --> 01:05:43,730
You said we'd go for another drink!

1036
01:05:50,112 --> 01:05:51,280
What's this?

1037
01:06:30,777 --> 01:06:32,154
Where am I?

1038
01:06:33,614 --> 01:06:36,283
Hold up. What's going on?

1039
01:06:36,617 --> 01:06:38,702
Why is the duvet black?

1040
01:06:43,415 --> 01:06:44,458
No.

1041
01:06:45,042 --> 01:06:47,794
No way. Did I sleep with him?

1042
01:06:48,879 --> 01:06:50,255
Did we do it?

1043
01:07:04,394 --> 01:07:05,395
What are you doing?

1044
01:07:07,022 --> 01:07:08,857
What? What are you doing there?

1045
01:07:10,108 --> 01:07:11,193
- Oh, gosh!
- Oh!

1046
01:07:19,117 --> 01:07:20,327
What is...

1047
01:07:21,161 --> 01:07:23,330
going on?

1048
01:07:24,998 --> 01:07:26,708
Oh, I...

1049
01:07:27,084 --> 01:07:28,919
I don't really know, either

1050
01:07:34,216 --> 01:07:36,051
but it looks like we're screwed.

1051
01:07:42,015 --> 01:07:44,810
THE PRACTICAL GUIDE TO LOVE

1052
01:07:51,775 --> 01:07:54,278
YOU WANT TO GO ON A DATE WITH ME?

1053
01:07:58,782 --> 01:08:02,369
THAT WAS TOO STRONG

1054
01:08:03,579 --> 01:08:06,373
DOES THE WIND TAKE AWAY ANGER?

1055
01:08:12,296 --> 01:08:15,757
NO, DON'T LEAVE ME

1056
01:08:18,802 --> 01:08:20,721
According to the witnesses

1057
01:08:21,138 --> 01:08:23,015
there wasn't just one man

1058
01:08:24,182 --> 01:08:26,435
but two!

1059
01:08:26,518 --> 01:08:28,186
I must've been out of my mind.

1060
01:08:28,312 --> 01:08:30,814
I'm not the type to be
all up in anyone's business

1061
01:08:30,897 --> 01:08:32,357
